{"author":"Claude","data":{"body":"OVERLAY CATALOG — performance\n- Source: Sentry performance-issue detector taxonomy (N+1 DB/API, slow query >500ms, large payload, main-thread I/O, render-blocking) = concepts; perflint(MIT)/Clippy(MIT-Apache)/PMD(BSD)/SpotBugs(LGPL taxonomy-ref); Google eng-practices complexity/over-engineering (CC-BY); Core Web Vitals; eslint-plugin-react-perf (MIT).\n- Dimensions: algorithmic/complexity regressions; data-access/IO amplification (N+1, chatty network, slow/unbounded query, blocking-IO-on-async) [highest signal]; allocations/copies; inefficient data structures; caching/memoization; unbounded growth/memory; concurrency appropriateness; frontend render budgets.\n- Triggers: DB/ORM/query-builder paths; loop-containing-a-call (AST = N+1); async/threadpool introductions; serialization/large-data; CURATED hot-path allowlist; frontend files.\n- FLAG (WEAK TRIGGERS — escalation-dependent): globs detect file-touches-DB, not introduced-N+1; big-O/memoization/unbounded-growth/premature-concurrency have NO reliable file/AST signature. Most base-escalation-reliant overlay. Two-tier: deterministic triggers = recall net for N+1/blocking-IO/large-payload/render-block; base-escalation for semantic dimensions.\n- LICENSE FLAG: don't vendor Semgrep registry rules (restrictive) — use perflint/Clippy/PMD."},"env_id":"a7f6c5e0-d538-4904-841a-a3fd102c21d7","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1781992352624281723,"uuid":"b0965a2c-05bd-40e4-ab18-fde241f80295"}